InteGrade (Version 0.5) - Tue Jun 23 2009 

* Local Usage Pattern Analyzer (LUPA)

* Integrade now can be used on Eclipse IDE.
	(Instructions on how to setup are located on the README file, located on the eclipse directory)

* Fixed BUG #32 - Compilation Bug on Ubuntu 8.04
	(http://ccsl.ime.usp.br/integrade/trac/ticket/32)

* Fixed BUG #33 - Execution descriptor is not loaded on parametric mode.
	(http://ccsl.ime.usp.br/integrade/trac/ticket/33)

* And some minor bug fixes

---------------------------------------------------------------------

InteGrade (Version 0.4) - Wed Oct 10 12:06:08 BRST 2007

* Support for MPI

* Initial integration of OppStore with InteGrade

* Execution Manager data is now persistent

* Refactored several method and variable names

* Many bug corrections

---------------------------------------------------------------------

InteGrade (Version 0.3) - Mon Jul 31 16:09:33 BRST 2006

* Splited the asctGui module into asct and gui modules

* Preliminary support for multiple clusters

* Support for checkpoint storage in remote repositories (CRM, ckpRepos)

* Refactoring in several modules

----------------------------------------------------------------------

InteGrade (Version 0.2) - Mon Nov 21 16:59:33 BRST 2005

* Name server (NFS is not required anymore)

* Security in Application Repository

* Improvements in asctGui

* Some bugs fixed and documentation updated

* Simplifications in installation procedures

----------------------------------------------------------------------

InteGrade (Version 0.1) - Fri Feb  4 14:52:38 BRST 2005

* This is the first InteGrade release!

* Support for BSMP communication in BSPlib.

* Documentation Updated.

* Improvements in InteGrade's BSPlib

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

